{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"44187429-7032-4e18-9346-fb9a996a0078","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_IrVCJz3QlCWfl1VghERxgG","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Configuring .NET crash dumps"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_rWcQvIDAHtsMFMzhaboUo2","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"echo \"Research done in-memory, providing config\"","description":"Preparing crash dump config","initial_wait":10},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Preparing crash dump config"}],"interactionId":"f6a3d3e3-9d83-400c-b0d1-e104db14e501","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me think about what's needed:\n\n1. **Environment variables** for .NET crash dump configuration\n2. **Kubernetes pod spec changes** (volume mounts, env vars, etc.)\n\nFor .NET crash dumps with NativeAOT, the key environment variables are:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` — enables automatic crash dump generation\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` — controls dump type (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` — path/pattern for the dump file\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics` — enable diagnostics for createdump itself\n\nI should note that `COMPlus_DbgEnableMiniDump` was the older naming convention before .NET 6+, so I'll want to use the `DOTNET_` prefix. For NativeAOT in .NET 8+, I need to explicitly point to the `createdump` tool since it's not bundled with the runtime, which means setting `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` to `/opt/tools/createdump`.\n\nNow I'm putting together a Kubernetes pod spec that configures these environment variables, sets up a volume for storing the crash dumps, and mounts it to the appropriate directory.\n\nWriting pod spec YAML...","outputTokens":537,"requestId":"502D:2C454F:24C8CB:2E6969:69F5547A"},"id":"0468b390-d72c-4364-95d1-a2c9901ec08e","timestamp":"